-- Brazil Studies Private Partnerships at Airports, Folha Says
-- B y   M a r i o   S e r g i o   L i m a
-- 2012-07-21T13:10:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/brazil-studies-private-partnerships-at-airports-folha-says.html
Dilma Rousseff’s government is
studying a way to develop partnerships with companies to operate
the nation’s airports without conceding the terminals
exclusively to private management,  Folha de S.Paulo  newspaper
said today, without saying where it got the information.  Rousseff wants a model in which the state-owned Infraero
would form a partnership with other companies to operate the
terminals, while Infraero would still having control of the
management, Folha said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mario Sergio Lima in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 mlima11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net  